issues.reproDescription:
The http-server-js emitter generates code that always requires the `content-type: application/json` header to be present, even when the request body is optional.

**Expected behavior**: When a request body is optional (marked with `?`), the generated handler should allow requests without a body AND without the `content-type` header.

**Actual behavior**: The generated handler in `src/generated/http/operations/server-raw.ts` contains code that checks:
```typescript
if (__contentType_7?.value !== "application/json") {
  return __ctx_2.errorHandlers.onInvalidRequest(...)
}
```
This check runs unconditionally, even when the body is optional and not provided. This means a POST request to `/optional-body` with no body and no `content-type` header will fail validation.

According to RFC specifications and the issue description, when a request body is optional, the `content-type` header should also be optional when the body is not provided.

